comm

Class Message

  • java.lang.Object
    • comm.Message
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BSHeartbeat, BSMotorSpeed, RHeartbeat

    public class Message
extends java.lang.Object
    A message representing a serializable remote-procedure-call with a name, integer id, and a variable list of values.

    • Method Detail

      • deserialize

        public static Message deserialize(java.io.InputStream in)
                           throws java.io.IOException,
                                  java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Attempts to construct a new Message object from the given InputStream. This is a blocking call and will wait on input from the stream. Note that calling deserialize() with a stream containing data resulting from calling serialize() on a Message must return a Message object which is equal to the original.
        Parameters:
        in - An input stream from which to attempt to read a message
        Returns:
        A message, if one could be successfully read from the given string. Null otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the input stream is no longer valid
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - if no message can be read yet
